    <text id="R155808T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Confederate Assistant Adjutant Robert Chilton writes Robert E. Lee, Commanding at
                    Staunton, in August, 1861, to notify him that supplies are being sent.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"> Gen. R. E. LEE, Staunton, Va.:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-08-26">August 26, 1861.</date>
                        <name type="place">RICHMOND,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>GEN.:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of War directs that you be informed that your requisitions for
                    clothing are being filled and the articles forwarded. He also wishes you to be
                    informed that Col. McDonald had previously to your orders to him been directed
                    to proceed with his regiment to Hampshire County, to carry out his original
                    instructions in that quarter, which were highly important.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am, sir, respectfully, your obedient servant,</salute>
                    <signed>R. H. CHILTON,<lb/> Assistant Adjutant-Gen.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
